\text{startingQuantity}\cdot\sum_{s=n-r+1}^n\frac1s
=5,n=4, r=3
5\cdot\sum_{s=2}^4\frac1s=5\left(\frac12+\frac13+\frac14\right)=\frac5{12}(6+4+3)=\frac{65}{12}
